    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION AXLES WITH CONTROLLED TRACTION
        DIFFERENTIALS: EATON - INSTALL - ADJUST DIFFERENTIAL BEARING PRELOAD
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="4">
        <title>ADJUST DIFFERENTIAL BEARING PRELOAD</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">At the teeth side of ring gear, position bearing adjuster until its first thread is visible
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401037">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401037" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401037" filename="../figg14/G1401037.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Position Bearing Adjuster</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">At the back face side of ring gear, tighten adjuster until there is no backlash.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">At the teeth side of ring gear, tighten adjuster until it contacts the bearing cup. Continue
                tightening adjuster two or three notches. This will preload bearings and provide backlash.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure backlash with a dial indicator (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401038">Figure 38</hotlnk>). Specifications are listed below.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401038" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401038" filename="../figg14/G1401038.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Measure Backlash With Dial Indicator</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">USED GEARING: Reset to backlash recorded before disassembly.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1"></para>
                <table id="hl1401005">
                    <title>Ring Gear Backlash Specifications</title>
                    <tgroup cols="2" colsep="1" rowsep="0">
                        <colspec colname="1" colwidth="3.58in"/>
                        <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.39in"/>
                        <spanspec namest="1" nameend="2" spanname="1to2"/>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry colspan="2" spanname="1to2">
                                    <para>NEW GEARING: Backlash should be as follows:</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Axles with 16 1/2" (419.1 mm) or smaller ring gear diameter:</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>0.006" to 0.016"</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>(0.152 to 0.406 mm)</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Axles with 18" (457.2 mm) ring gears:</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>0.008" to 0.018"</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>(0.203 to 0.457 mm)</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Paint ring gear teeth and check tooth contact pattern. Correct tooth patterns are
                illustrated in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401039">Figure 39</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401040">Figure 40</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401039" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401039" filename="../figg14/G1401039.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Correct Pattern (Used Gearing)</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1401040" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401040" filename="../figg14/G1401040.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Correct Pattern (New Gearing)</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For detailed instructions on checking and adjusting procedures, refer to the appropriate Eaton
                        service manual covering your specific axle.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With ring gear and pinion adjusted correctly, align adjusters and locks, then tighten
                differential bearing cap bolts to 360 to 440 ft-lbs. (488 to 596 N&#8226;m). Install cotter pin in one
                adjuster lock. Install bolts in opposite adjuster lock and tighten to 160 to 176 ft-lbs. (217 to 239 N&#8226;m).
                Lockwire bearing and adjuster lock bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">Seasonal and Driver-Controlled CTD Only:</emph>
                Position shift fork in carrier opening, then install sliding clutch. With clutch installed, engage shift
                fork yoke with clutch collar. Then install shift fork shaft. Install expansion plugs to seal openings.
                Install shift fork seal and spring over end of shift fork. Move shift fork to place sliding clutch in
                engaged position. (Sliding clutch must be engaged to allow installation of carrier on housing.)
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
